<p>I've spent the past few years talking about <a href="https://consequencedesign.com">consequence design,</a> but my personal research practice is focused on service design & delivery and policy. I'm director of design at 18F, board president for the Portland chapter of AIGA and (starting in January 2024), an intermittent lecturer at the University of Michigan Taubman College of Architecture and Urban Planning.</p>
<p>
 Since initially introducing the consequence design framework a few years ago, I've researched how generative AI platforms, prompt engineering, and combinatory impacts of interaction architectures have been destablizing forces that policy isn't adept at navigating due to the speed of digital platforms. I've mostly used discursive design to interrogate this unraveling through a critical lens, speculating on possible futures and reflecting on the inadquacies of the current policy infrastructure to solve for these unimagined futures. 
</p>
<p>
